    "body" : "<p>code extracted from <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/i18n/format/numberFormat.html\">this link</a> ;</p>\n\n<pre><code>Double amount = new Double(345987.246);\nNumberFormat numberFormatter;\nString amountOut;\n\nnumberFormatter = NumberFormat.getNumberInstance(currentLocale);\namountOut = numberFormatter.format(amount);\nSystem.out.println(amountOut + \" \" + \n                   currentLocale.toString());\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The output from this example shows how the format of the same number varies with Locale: </p>\n\n<pre><code>345 987,246  fr_FR\n345.987,246  de_DE\n345,987.246  en_US\n</code></pre>\n"
